entry.def: If you refer to someone as an old-timer, you mean that he or she has been living in a particular place or doing a particular job for a long time.

example.ex: The old-timers and established families clutched the reins of power.
example.tran: 久居此地的居民和根基稳固的家族牢牢掌控着权力。

entry.def: An old man is sometimes referred to as an old-timer .

example.ex: The old-timers used to recall how hot 1886 was.
example.tran: 老人们常常回想起1886年的酷热。

means.word_mean: 1. an experienced person who has been through many battles; someone who has given long service
